      <hedline>
        <hl1>Internal Exam</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cynthia Munro Pyle letter disputes May 7 Ethicist column giving advice to physician treating husband and wife1</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was shocked to read The Ethicist (May 7) giving a physician advice on how to avoid a knotty situation. It is hard to imagine an ''old-fashioned physician'' shying away from responsibility. The adult approach would have been to lecture the husband and to tell the wife about her infection.</p>
        <p>Cynthia Munro Pyle  New York</p>
      </block>
